I've read somewhere and I can't find the source anymore that, if a product starts selling in a variety of colors, instead of one (usually black) or two (black or white), it's innovation cycle is basically done. You can expect only incremental updates and very few innovative things.

Is it a thing? Are there any studies about this?

It makes sense to me, but I would like some sources.
